creator: Saint Augustine of Hippo
description:
LibriVox recording of Confessionum Libri Tredecim by Saint Augustine of Hippo.
Read in Latin by bedwere

Confessions (Latin: Confessiones) is the name of an autobiographical work, consisting of 13 books, by St. Augustine of Hippo, written between AD 397 and AD 398. Modern English translations of it are sometimes published under the title The Confessions of St. Augustine in order to distinguish the book from other books with similar titles. Its original title was "Confessions in Thirteen Books", and it was composed to be read out loud with each book being a complete unit. (Summary by Wikipedia)
For further information, including links to M4B audio book, online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
subject: librivox; audiobooks;poetry; poems
title: Confessionum Libri Tredecim

reviews.reviewbody: Lovers of the Latin language will be more than grateful for this latest Librivox contribution.  Highest praise to the reader and more gratitude than I can express.
reviews.reviewtitle: Many, many thanks tio the reader
